The writer of this work was DAvm Hmnz of Gonsonom, the well known author of the History of the House and Race of Douglas and Augus. He was the second son of Sir David, the seventh of the Barons of &Vedderburm whose deeds are recorded in these pages‚ and much of what is known of his early life will be found interspersed in the account which he gives of his bro- ther, the eighth baron. He was born, it is usually supposed, about the year 1560. In examining the records of the Uni- versity of St Andrews, we find that David Hume was incorpo- rated as a student in St Leonard’s College in the year 15783 and, from the correspondence of time, there is no reason to doubt that this was our author, who afterwards designated him- self by the title of leeagrius, or of Godseroft, the name of his property, which he is said to have adopted instead of Gowks- croft, as it was formerly called.
